column4: "If I Should Lose You"
"dougmck@TPG.com.au - in the Bill Evans trio style - see Old Real Book Vol 2  - p155\012"
"Last 8 bars rubato as intro"
"Drop 2 block chords - melody surrounds  chord tones here  (F  and then Bb) "
"- lower neighbour is chromatic / upper neighbour diatonic"
"Dim chord on upper and lower neighbours"
"Nice dom (F7) to tonic (Bb) cadence using 4th voicings."
"In tempo for head on first chorus"
"Bass plays freely but is more or less in 2."
"Drums played freely - no regular Hi - hat on offbeats -  rides pickup the rhythms of piano or bass"
"Gm11then Gbm11then Fm11 - using this voicing - LH  b3
"Little figure that 'surrounds' the C tonic on Cm9 chord"
"Bill Evans 'ish' - finishing a phrase on a nice colour tone rather than chord tone -  here the #11"
"This phrase finishes on the 9th"
"3 note phrase on Gm7 - diatonic -  moves to rhythmically similar  3 note scale fragments  "
"Chromatic figure on Gm7 begins on 11th ends on 9th"
"Another 3 note figure that is echo-ed but not quite so diatonically"
"'Drummer' picks up the phrase"
"Sliding off black notes on to white"
"Another 3 note figure moves around"
"Increases in intensity as it rises"
"Back to head on last 8 bars"
"Piano"
"Bass(Acoustic or Fretless)"
